=# Task

Your task is to consider the following user query and then consider the following metadata keys with example values that we have that we can limit our result set from.

# Metadata Filters and Possible Values

{{ $json.filterPromptInstructions }}

# Metadata Operators

The following operators are allowed:

>
<
=
!=
>=
<=
IN
NOT IN

IF IN or NOT IN are provided, then an array of values must be provided.

Now output a filter array with relevant filters with the following example format. The below filter_categories are just for exampe purposes. Use the "Metadata Filters and Possible Values" list above for the list of allowed filters.

[
    "filter": {
      "$and": [
        {
          "category": {
            "operator": "IN",
            "value": [
              "F1",
              "Rally"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "year": {
            "operator": ">",
            "value": 2024
          }
        }
      ]
    }
]

If the query does not have relevant metadatafilters, then do not output any ... for example

{
  "filter": {}
}

If there is only 1 relevant metadafilter, then just output that ... for example

[
    "filter": {
      "$and": [
        {
          "motorsport_category": {
            "operator": "IN",
            "value": [
              "F1",
              "Rally"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
]

Only output in JSON

Note: Today's date is {{ $now }}

